HTML (Day 1)
1. Introduction to HTML
- Definition: HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is a standard markup language used to create web pages.
- Explanation: HTML is used to structure and organize content on the web, including text, images, videos, and more.

2. Basic HTML Structure
- Definition: The basic HTML structure consists of a declaration, a root element, a head section, and a body section.
- Explanation: The declaration (<!DOCTYPE html>) specifies the document type, the root element (<html>) contains all the other elements, the head section (<head>) contains metadata about the document, and the body section (<body>) contains the content of the HTML document.

3. HTML Headings
- Definition: HTML headings are used to define headings of different levels.
- Explanation: There are six levels of headings in HTML, ranging from <h1> (main heading) to <h6> (sub-sub-sub-subheading).

4. HTML Paragraphs
- Definition: HTML paragraphs are used to define a paragraph of text.
- Explanation: The <p> element is used to contain a paragraph of text, and can be styled using CSS.

CSS (Day 1)
1. Introduction to CSS
- Definition: CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is a styling language used to control the layout and appearance of web pages.
- Explanation: CSS is used to separate presentation from structure, making it easier to maintain and update web pages.

2. Basic CSS Syntax
- Definition: The basic CSS syntax consists of a selector, a property, and a value.
- Explanation: The selector identifies the element(s) to be styled, the property specifies the aspect of the element to be styled, and the value specifies the style to be applied.

3. CSS Colors
- Definition: CSS colors are used to specify the color of text, backgrounds, and other elements.
- Explanation: Colors can be specified using color names (e.g. "red", "blue"), hexadecimal values (e.g. "#FF0000", "#0000FF"), or RGB values (e.g. "rgb(255, 0, 0)", "rgb(0, 0, 255)).

4. CSS Backgrounds
- Definition: CSS backgrounds are used to specify the background color or image of an element.
- Explanation: The background-color property is used to specify the background color of an element, while the background-image property is used to specify the background image.

Answers to Questions
Q: What does HTML stand for?
A: HyperText Markup Language

Q: What is the purpose of the <!DOCTYPE html> declaration?
A: To declare the document type as HTML5

Q: What is the difference between <h1> and <h2>?
A: <h1> is a main heading, while <h2> is a subheading

Q: What is the purpose of the body element?
A: To contain the content of the HTML document

Q: What is the basic syntax of a CSS rule?
A: selector { property: value; }

Q: What is the purpose of the background-color property?
A: To set the background color of an element